                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1168">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Assis-Brasil</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Day</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of Brazil</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Block Island</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your excellency’s note of the 15th instant, containing some suggestions
                    respecting the naval observances for neutral men-of-war in ports now blockaded
                    or which may hereafter be blockaded by the American Navy during the war with
                    Spain. I shall transmit a copy of said note to my Government.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. F. de, Assis-Brasil.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
